CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1782236889
OL,3,CMajor incident declared after
OL,4,Cexplosions heard and smoke plumes seen
OL,5,Cfor miles
OL,7,FOne man, who lives on Ditchfield Road,
OL,8,Ftold the Liverpool Echo that he heard
OL,9,F"loads of bangs" before looking out of
OL,10,Fhis back window and seeing the smoke
OL,11,Frising.
OL,13,FA taxi driver who was over the road
OL,14,Ffrom the scene at Speke Road added,
OL,15,F"The entire sky over Liverpool is
OL,16,Fturning black and multiple explosions
OL,17,Fare currently taking place. It is a
OL,18,Fbig fire.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
